    {
      "type": "prose",
      "title": "Summary",
      "content": "Adds a full role-based access control (RBAC) system on top of the JWT auth layer introduced in PR #42. Users are now assigned one or more roles (`admin`, `editor`, `viewer`), and API routes declare their required permissions via a `@requireRole` decorator.\n\nThe implementation follows a **policy-based model**: roles map to permission sets defined in `src/rbac/policies.ts`, making it easy to add new roles without touching route code. An `admin` dashboard route is included for managing user roles.\n\n### Key decisions\n\n- Roles stored in JWT claims (no extra DB lookup on each request)\n- Permission checks happen *after* token validation in the middleware chain\n- Superadmin bypass via `SUPERADMIN_EMAILS` env variable for emergency access\n- `403 Forbidden` responses include the missing permission for easier debugging"
    },
